HoraHub — attributions

The interpretation rules in kb/ are HoraHub's own encoding of classical Jyotiṣa
principles, written in original wording. They draw on the following sources for
their underlying ideas. Attribution credits these works; it does not include or
redistribute their text, and no copyrighted translation is shipped in this repo.

  • Maharṣi Parāśara, Bṛhat Parāśara Horā Śāstra (BPHS) — the underlying Sanskrit
    verses are an ancient, public-domain text. The R. Santhanam English
    translation, where consulted, is copyrighted by its publisher and is NOT
    redistributed here.
  • Robert Svoboda, "Light on Life: An Introduction to the Astrology of India" —
    copyright the author/publisher; consulted only, not reproduced.

Source PDFs belong in the git-ignored /kb/sources directory and must never be
committed. See docs/CONTRIBUTING.md and docs/KB_PIPELINE.md.

Astronomical calculations use orbital-element methods after Paul Schlyter
("Computing planetary positions"), a freely published algorithm.
